block content
  p Landing pages are simple. I’ve made hundreds. It was my old job, then I did it for clients.
  p When I started I was clueless. Throwing shapes on a page and crossing my fingers. But after a few dozen I found a formula that converted. Here it is:
  p.list.list__top 1/ Explain the value you provide!{' '}
    span.italic (title)
  p.list 2/ Explain how you'll create it!{' '}
    span.italic (subtitle)
  p.list 3/ Let the user visualise it!{' '}
    span.italic (image)
  p.list 4/ Make it believable!{' '}
    span.italic (social proof)
  p.list.list__bottom 5/ Make taking the next step easy!{' '}
    span.italic (CTA)
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/lsp1a.png" alt="Marketing Examples Product Hunt").img__100
  p Let's go into on each component.
  h2.slab.bg1 1/ Title
  p There’s 50 ways to write a great title. The majority fall into two categories.
  p
    span.bold 1/ Value + Hook
  p
    span.italic Explain the value you provide. Add a hook to make it more appetising. There’s two ways to write hooks:
  p.inwardSpeech a) Ask “what can we say about our product that no-one else can?” That’s your hook.
  span.isBreak
  p.inwardSpeech b) Ask, “what's stopping people buying?”. Address this objection. That’s your hook.
  //- p.inwardSpeech b) Indentify your customer's biggest buying objection. Address it. That’s your hook.
  //- p
  //-   span.bold 2/ One line summary
  //- p
  //-   span.italic The goal is to own your niche in one line. The trick is conviction. Write like you’ve got no competitors.
  //- p
  //-   span.italic Boil what you do into a line so powerful you don’t need a hook. The goal is to own your niche. Write like you’ve got no competitors.
  p
    span.bold 2/ Own your niche
  p
    span.italic Boil what you do into a line so powerful you don’t need a hook. The trick is conviction. Write like you’ve got no competitors.
  //- p.inwardSpeech • Don’t say “We help” say “It's how”.<br>• Don’t say “A” say “The”.
  h2.slab.bg2 2/ Subtitle
  p Good subtitles do two things:
  p.list.list__top a) Introduce the product
  p.list.list__bottom b) Explain!{' '}
    span.bold how
    |!{' '}it creates the value in your title
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/lsp2b.png" alt="Marketing Examples Product Hunt").img__100
  h2.slab.bg4 3/ Image
  p Your image is your chance to show off your product. Don’t waste it with stock images or illustrations.
  p.inwardSpeech The greatest thing to be achieved in advertising is believability, and nothing is more believable than the product itself — Leo Burnett
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/lsp3.png" alt="Marketing Examples Product Hunt").img__100
  p Show off your product. Make me want it. Don’t rely on stock images or illustrations.
  h2.slab.bg3 4/ Social Proof
  p Good social proof shows credibility. Great social proof inspires action.
  p It's not “a box to be ticked”. It's an opportunity to sell your product. Think!{' '}
    mark.ss4 real customers
    | ,!{' '}
    mark.ss1 real words
    |,!{' '}
    mark.ss3 real numbers.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/lsp4a.png" alt="Marketing Examples Product Hunt").img__100
