  h2.slab.bg5 5/ CTA
  p The role of the CTA is to make taking the next step easy.
  p Most buttons amplify action:!{' '}
    span.italic Sign Up, Start Trial etc.
    |!{' '} They're clear, but not compelling. Here's 3 more persuasive button types.
  //- Lon
  p
    span.bold 1/ Call to value
  p.inwardSpeech Fulfils!{' '}
    span.bold the value
    |!{' '}promised in your title. Buttons which emphasise “value” over “action” usually perform better.
  //- p.inwardSpeech Emphasises “value” over “action”.
  p
    span.bold 2/ Remove friction
  p.inwardSpeech Use the second half of the button to handle an objection. E.g. “I bet this takes ages” ⟶ “with one click”
  p.inwardSpeech Add a few words to the CTA to entice the user to click.
  p
    span.bold 3/ CTA + Email capture
